This paper deals with the problem of classification in computer vision, which is a common topic in the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the theoretical analysis of the top-k error, which is related to the sub-category of cryptography and security (cs.CR) and information theory (cs.IT).
